# [WORD SISTER](https://github.com/kaihendry/wordsister)

<img alt="Jutta Hendry" src="http://graph.facebook.com/anotherjutta/picture?type=large">

My sister needed a simple Web page to add Wedding information upon. The options
sucked, so I wrote this.

## Features

[HTML](http://whatwg.org/html) isn't hard, though it's easier to edit with Markdown
with a [preview](http://markdown.pioul.fr/).

Editing a page on the Web is accomplished by appending <a href="/edit">/edit</a> to the URL.

First HTML comment becomes the page title.

You can also edit the `*.mdwn` directly on the filesystem. Just run `make` in the top level directory when done.

There is a simple text area to edit the <a href="style.css">style.css</a> and
an ability to upload files.

## Install

Git clone to your [VirtualDocumentRoot directory](http://dabase.com/e/04025/), and away you go. Requires [Apache](https://github.com/kaihendry/wordsister/blob/master/.htaccess), PHP, `make` & a `markdown` binary.

    cd /srv/www
    vhost=ws.dabase.com
    git clone git@github.com:kaihendry/wordsister.git $vhost
    cd $vhost
    chown -R :www-data .
    chmod g+s .
    # to keep your changes optionally in source control
    git checkout -b $vhost

## Demo

Resets on the hour: <http://ws.dabase.com/> with the cronjob:

	@hourly cd /srv/www/ws.dabase.com; umask 002; git checkout .; git clean -d -f; git pull > /dev/null ;make > /dev/null
